From: Hermes Agent <hermes@nousresearch.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 23:00:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] oplus_charger: Skip chargerid switch during VOOC active to
 prevent MCU communication errors

The usbtemp_kthread periodically calls smbchg_set_chargerid_switch_val(0)
to measure USB temperature. When VOOC fast charging is active, this
disconnects the charger ID switch and disrupts communication with the
VOOC MCU over the data GPIO (gpio 93), causing 'data err:0x70' and
subsequent charger suspend.

Fix by skipping chargerid switch manipulation when fast charging
(VOOC/SVOOC) is active.

Signed-off-by: Hermes Agent <hermes@nousresearch.com>
---
 drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c | 15 ++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c b/drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c
index f37d9b1c0..a8e3c2f4b 100644
--- a/drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c
+++ b/drivers/power/oppo/oplus_charger.c
@@ -6213,14 +6213,23 @@ static void oplus_chg_get_chargerid_voltage(struct oplus_chg_chip *chip)
 		charger_xlog_printk(CHG_LOG_CRTI,
 			"get charger id from mcu, chip->chargerid_volt = %d\n",
 			chip->chargerid_volt);
-	} else {
+	}
+
+	/* Don't touch chargerid switch if VOOC fast charging is active -
+	 * doing so disconnects the data GPIO and kills MCU communication,
+	 * causing "data err:0x70" and unwanted charger suspend.
+	 */
+	if (oplus_vooc_get_fastchg_started() == true) {
+		charger_xlog_printk(CHG_LOG_CRTI,
+			"fastchg active, skip chargerid switch\n");
+	} else if (chip->charger_exist) {
 		if (chip->chg_ops->get_chargerid_switch_val() == 0) {
 			chip->chg_ops->set_chargerid_switch_val(1);
 			oplus_vooc_set_vooc_chargerid_switch_val(1);
 			msleep(100);
 			chip->chargerid_volt = oplus_chg_chargerid_voltage_check(chip);
 		}
-	}
 
 	charger_xlog_printk(CHG_LOG_CRTI,
 		"get charger id, chip->chargerid_volt = %d, charger_exist = %d\n",
